# Project: hans-crafted-stories (Sovereign AI Empire)

## What this project IS
- A React 18 + Vite + TypeScript web app (NOT the n8n monorepo)
- Personal portfolio site at hansvanleeuwen.com
- Portal: admin dashboard with SEO tools, content CMS, user management
- Empire: infrastructure monitoring dashboard (7-layer health grid)
- HansAI: terminal-style AI command center

## Tech stack
- Frontend: React 18, Vite 5, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 3, shadcn/ui (Radix), Framer Motion
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Edge Functions, Realtime)
- AI Gateway: Lovable AI Gateway (Gemini models) for edge function chat
- Hosting: Cloudflare (Workers, Zero Trust, DNS)

## Infrastructure (external, managed via dashboard)
- VPS 1 (srv1402218.hstgr.cloud / 187.124.1.75): n8n at n8n.hansvanleeuwen.com, MCP Gateway, Loki/Grafana
- VPS 2 (srv1411336.hstgr.cloud / 187.124.2.66): Ollama + Open WebUI (AI Brain)
- Local: Windows 11, GTX 1660 Ti, 24 GB RAM, Ollama, Docker Desktop

## Key directories
- src/pages/ — Route pages (Portal, Empire, HansAI, About, Blog)
- src/components/portal/ — Portal tool system (26+ components)
- src/components/empire/ — Empire monitoring (status grid, audit trail, quick actions, Claude panel)
- src/components/hansai/ — HansAI terminal components
- supabase/functions/ — Edge functions (empire-health, hansai-chat, n8n-agent, portal-api, etc.)
- public/empire/ — VPS bootstrap files (CLAUDE.md, docker-compose.yml, setup.sh)
- public/workflows/ — n8n workflow JSONs and install scripts

## 7-Layer Sovereign AI Spine
1. Shield — Cloudflare Zero Trust
2. Portal — hansvanleeuwen.com (this React app)
3. Brain — n8n Orchestration (VPS 1)
4. Muscle — Claude Code CLI (VPS 1, tmux session)
5. Senses — Docker MCP Gateway (VPS 1, port 3100)
6. Memory — Supabase database
7. Immune — AI Doctor / Edge Functions

## Response style
- Always use numbered lists and clear steps
- Be direct and honest about what works and what doesn't
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- When suggesting infrastructure changes, remember this is a React dashboard — the actual infra lives on the VPSs
